This is a Tic Tac Toe game written in Ruby using TDD.

The game decides randomly who goes first, the computer or the human player.

To make your move type a number between 1-9 representing the box you want to place a mark in.

The objective was to create a game where the computer would not lose.

Ruby version: ruby 2.0.0p247

Player marks can be set in player_marks.rb

To run the game:
  $ ruby ttt.rb

To run the specs:
  $ gem install rspec
  $ rspec spec